<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 5:34AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog for the Early Morning Commute...
Areas of fog will continue to develop through sunrise.
Visibilities below one mile will occur in some areas, along with
pockets of locally dense fog reducing visibilities to one quarter
mile or less. Conditions are expected to improve by mid morning.
If traveling this morning in foggy areas, slow down and be
prepared for rapid changes in visibility. Use low beam headlights
if driving, and leave plenty of distance between you and the
vehicle ahead.</description>
